  "articleSummary": "This article provides a step-by-step tutorial for securing a Docker host on Debian/Ubuntu using UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall). It covers installing UFW and nmap, retrieving IP addresses, configuring default deny incoming rules with selective outbound allowances (SSH, HTTP, DNS, Docker bridge), and enabling the firewall with a caution against locking out SSH. The guide then demonstrates testing the firewall with nmap scans to verify only intended ports are open. The intended audience is Docker host administrators seeking a practical, command-line-driven firewall setup.",
